  "description": [
    "THE MORNING APPEAL CARSON NEVADA Published every morning Monday excepted H R MIGHELS Lessee and Publisher OFFICE THE APPEAL BLDG CORNER OF MAIN A 2d STREETS TELEPHONE MAIN 351 TERMS One year by mail 8 00 Six months by mail 4 00 Three months by mail 2 00 Per week by carrier 25 Entered at the Carson Nevada post office as second class matter THE PRESIDENTS MESSAGE INCE the day that President Roosevelt took his seat the peo cle irrespective of nartv have held opinions to themselves until his message should be made public The document is now in the hands of the people and is being given the closest study that a message has had in many years The present condition of trusts and combinations of wealth combined with the activity of anarchy were the problems that the common people wished to see handled The President in his message makes recommendations in both in stances that if acted on by Congress will result in a remedy The Chinese exclusion problem meets with the approval of the people of the West as it is emphatic The most vital question to the West irrigation of arid territory is given unusual prominence"
  ],
